    "componentSelection": "Appbar, bottom-navigation, and list-item components are selected from the Figma design system to maintain consistency and leverage pre-built styling.  Component Node IDs are used to reference these specific components in the Figma file.",
    "styleApplication": "Text and color styles are applied according to the design specifications.  Primary color styles are used for actions, secondary colors for supportive elements, and neutral colors for body text. Component-level styling is prioritized; textStyle properties are only added to native-text elements.  Color styles are referenced by name for consistency and maintainability.",
    "designSystemMapping": "The design system components are used wherever possible. Custom components are avoided for maintainability. All components are directly instantiated without unnecessary wrapper elements.",
    "variantDecisions": "Variants are used within list-item components to control the presence of trailing icons, supporting text, and other visual elements based on the specific needs of each setting option.  The \"Condition\" variant determines if the list item displays one or two lines of content. \"Leading\", \"Trailing\", and \"Show supporting text\" variants are used to control visual elements such as icons and supporting text."
  }
}
